# Transfer Convex Custody to joelclaw-api

## Question

Execute the custody decision from the [charter](./charter-joelclaw-api.svx): move the `convex/` directory (schema, functions, deployment config, admin credentials) from `apps/web` in the joelclaw monorepo into `joelclaw-api`, making joelclaw-api the sole deployer of the existing self-hosted deployment on :3210. apps/web keeps direct Convex reads, consuming the generated client/types from joelclaw-api via `link:` (same seam as joelclaw-video→system-bus). Consult `/skill:local-convex` before touching the deployment. Verification is the hard part and is non-negotiable: after the move, (1) `convex deploy` from joelclaw-api succeeds against :3210 with an unchanged schema hash, (2) apps/web typechecks and its pages still read (vaultNotes, contentResources, systemStatus paths exercised), (3) nothing references the old apps/web/convex path. Watch for: codegen output location, env var custody (CONVEX_URL, admin key — where leased from), and the monorepo's tsconfig/biome exclusions for the departed directory. Other sessions work in the monorepo concurrently — touch only what the move requires, never `git add -A`. Resolved when the readback proves all three checks and the resolution records the new deploy command, where credentials live, and the apps/web dep wiring.
